<TITLE> Satkhira BDR verdict due on Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Satkhira, Apr 18 (bdnews24.com)  Verdict on the mutiny charges against 60 BDR members in Satkhira is set to be given on Monday. It will be the fourth of its kind. Earlier, verdicts were given out against Panchagarh, Thakurgaon and Feni BDR members. The accused were charged with rebelling on Feb 26 in support of their comrades in Pilkhana, Dhaka where the rebellion of Feb 25-26, 2009 saw about 70 people dead, including 57 army officers deputed to the BDR. Sixteen of the accused riflesmen admitted their guilt when the procedure began on Dec 7 last year. The trial ended on Mar 23. BDR director Gen Mainul Islam, head of the judges panel, is set to give the verdict at 11am on Monday at the special court, situated at 41 Rifles Battalion headquarters. The two other members of the judges panel are Lt Col Gazi Md Khalid and Maj Lutful Kabir. Deputy attorney general Khasruzzaman is filling in for the attorney general. On Nov 15, the government formed six special courts, including two in Dhaka, to try some 3,500 border guards accused in some 40 cases around the country. bdnews24.co
